ext","text":"(K;) in the dial. of the Benoo-Málik: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who eats alone, and withholds his drinking-bowl"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raifodahu","text_ar":"رَِفْدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and beats his slave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kh, L, K:) all these meanings are assigned to it in the verse [6 of ch. c.] of the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a A@loA_inosaAna lirab~ihi lakanuwdN","text_ar":"اـِنَّ ا@لْاـِنْسَانَ لِرَبِّهِ لَكَنُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but of the last, ISd remarks, that he knows no foundation for it in the classical language, and that it is not easily admissible coupled with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lrb~h","text_ar":"لربّه"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.) ―         -b2-  A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ungrateful for friendship, and for loving communion, commerce,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intercourse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunudN","text_ar":"كُنُدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (As, L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN kanuwdN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ كَنُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land that produces nothing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K.)"}],"source_refs":["L","S","A","Zj","K","TA","Kh"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%83%D9%86%D9%88%D8%AF/","headword_ar":"كنود","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23527#f8db5c","body_html":"<span>الكنود: هو الذي يعد المصائب وينسى المواهب.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_39","lexicon_en":"ʿAbdullāh ibn ʿAbbās, Gharīb al-Qurʾān fī Shiʿr al-ʿArab, also known as Masāʾil Nāfiʿ b. al-Azraq (d. 687 CE)","lexicon_ar":"غريب القرآن في شعر العرب لعبد الله بن عباس","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23527#575938","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">ك ن د [لكنود]</span><br><span>قال: يا ابن عباس: أخبرني عن قول الله عزّ وجلّ: إِنَّ الْإِنْسانَ لِرَبِّهِ لَكَنُودٌ .</span><br><span>قال: الكفور النعم: وهو الذي يكفر وجده ، ويمنع رفده ، ويجيع عبده.</span><br><span>قال: وهل تعرف العرب ذلك؟</span><br><span>قال: نعم، أما سمعت الشاعر وهو يقول:</span><br><span>شكرت له يوم العكاظ نواله </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> ولم أك للمعروف ثمّ كنودا </span>"}]}}